Chemicals in Cosmetics

Sanchita Rathi

2022-19-12

Introduction

COSMETICS A “cosmetic” is any substance used to clean, improve or change the complexion, skin, hair or, nails Cosmetics include beauty preparations (make-up, perfume, skin cream, nail polish).

CHEMICALS Artificially made substance that is used in or produced by a reaction involving changes to atoms or molecules which manipulates the formation when added in another substance.

Introduction

CORRELATION (Chemicals in Cosmetics)

  • Added Colors
  • Appealing fragrance
  • Artificial ingredients

Objectives

To identify the relationship between the Chemicals and Cosmetics based on:

  • Chemical Range
  • Product categories and Sub categories
  • Brand or Company names

Data Source

  • The data set consists of 100 samples
  • Data set taken from kaggle.com

Project Description

  • Descriptive Analysis: Treemaps, Columncharts
  • Extracted Analysis (Implications) : Pie Charts, Density Chart, BarChart

Division of Cosmetic Categories

  • Tree Map of Primary Category by Price
  • Skin Care Products are the most Pricy
  • Hair Coloring Product cost the lowest among other Products

Division of Subcategories

  • Tree Map of Primary Category with their Sub-Category
  • Under Skin care products, Skin moisturizers costs the most followed by Make up products

Division of Chemical Names

  • Tree Map of Chemicals by their amount in each product category
  • Nail Products have high amount of Titanium dioxide
  • Fragnances catergoy seems to have the least amount of Titanium Oxide

Chemical Levels by Molecular Weight

  • Column Chart of Products Status by Chemical Quantity (out of 100 products)
  • Most Products falls under Safe Status based on the Chemical Quantity of 0 to 80 g/mol
  • We do have Toxic products present among 100 products ranging toxicity level from 451 to 600 g/mol
## 
## Alarming     Safe    Toxic   Unsafe 
##        3       82        8        6

Cost Levels by Price

  • Column Chart of Price Status by Products (out of 100 products)
  • Most of the Cosmetics Products are affordable
## 
##     Average       Cheap       Pricy Very Costly

Weight Staus vs Price Status

  • Stacked bar chart of relationship between Chemical Status VS Price Status
  • Safe or Toxic Cosmetics generally have every range of products available from cheap to very costly price category

Popular Categories

  • Donut Chart of Cosmetics Categories
  • Nail Products are the most popular category

Common Chemicals

  • Pie-Chart on commonly used Chemicals in Cosmetics Products
  • Titanium Dioxide is populary used chemical

Harmful Chemicals

  • Density Chart on Chemicals by Weight (g/mol)
  • Cocamide Diethanolmine has the highest density chemical by weight if used in products

Top Companies

  • Bar Chart of Companies Name which use greater amount of Concentrated Chemicals
  • GOJO Industries use maximum amount of chemicals (molecular weight) in their products

Conclusion

  • Chemicals are evidently present in cosmetics
  • Luxurious products includes higher weightage of chemicals.
  • Knowledge on the commonly used chemicals
  • Better decision making among consumers

Recommendations

  • Awareness among consumers
  • Smart Purchasing
  • Choose Health over luxury
  • Always Check chemical ingredients.
